{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/haemorrhoids/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"f3593aa4-5cf3-58eb-8ccc-86cb2a10a70b","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 3af291d0-6042-47ef-a3b7-a7f20187e092 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 3af291d0-6042-47ef-a3b7-a7f20187e092 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item dbe73880-5f4f-4572-971c-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field c0e1dcc4-3f17-4c23-b2db-a7f20187e092 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field c0e1dcc4-3f17-4c23-b2db-a7f20187e092 --><!-- begin field 7dd22707-971b-4013-9f28-a7f20187e092 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 7dd22707-971b-4013-9f28-a7f20187e092 --><!-- begin field 7bfc7766-c8c2-4b69-b68f-a7f20187e092 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 7bfc7766-c8c2-4b69-b68f-a7f20187e092 --><!-- begin field 5db1dee1-920a-487d-9ddb-a7f20187e092 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 5db1dee1-920a-487d-9ddb-a7f20187e092 --><!-- begin field cfc2b401-2cd1-4240-bdd8-a7f20187e092 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field cfc2b401-2cd1-4240-bdd8-a7f20187e092 --><!-- begin field 3bcf7fa9-1728-4c33-aac1-a7f20187e092 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 3bcf7fa9-1728-4c33-aac1-a7f20187e092 --><!-- end item dbe73880-5f4f-4572-971c-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"f7906562-4fee-5a84-8303-379c1264e3a1","topicId":"602684c2-aefe-47f4-8cd4-a073fae976fd","topicName":"Haemorrhoids","slug":"haemorrhoids","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2016","chapters":[{"id":"9349c3d4-585b-5a5c-9330-84732a59d51d","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"52331225-5fe4-5e5c-93e3-001e75392b51","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"c45a7da5-46fd-508b-9e45-f98e7d939a1d","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"b1223559-471e-54d8-8c83-8189eb61fc94","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e821eb1c-58f1-534b-a58c-3b9052710878","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"1244c725-1653-55ce-8c72-e37d3ac00ba8","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"38a8aa2e-e227-570e-b068-d52250cc56b1","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"9654ebf6-8b46-59c9-943d-7896c69c2423","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"9ee0ecc3-8f67-5568-805d-353603370077","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"